    Dieter F. Uchtdorf, Your Potential, Your Privilege</blockquote>
  <p>
    As professional Web Developers we are responsible to develop a set of core skills that when combined with divine help will allow us to deliver world class products.  We have identified those skills to be HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Testing and Performance, and Frontier.
  </p>
  <p>
    To help in our skills development, we have created a FamilySearch Web Development Guild.  The guild provides a framework for our learning and advancement.  Below we provide a list of skill levels, their definitions, and what is required to attain them.
  </p>

  <img src="<%- img('guildPyramid.png') %>" alt="Guild Pyramid" />

  <h3>FamilySearch Guild Achievement Levels:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
        <h4>Apprentice</h4>
        <p>
          An apprentice is concerned about understanding and remembering.  We will recommend material to study and tutorials you can take.  As a way to capture your leaning and to demonstrate your skills, you will be asked to start a portfolio of your examples.  Through this work, an apprentice will demonstrate their knowledge of core concepts and ability to perform basic skills.  As an alternative to portfolio work, a developer can use previous projects or production work to satisfy all or part of these requirements.  Previous work needs to be reviewed and approved.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4>Journeman</h4>
      <p>
        A journeyman is actively applying their knowledge in daily production work and in new and creative ways.  You will have the chance to continue to demonstrate your ability as you add to your portfolio. Through additional work, a journeyman will demonstrate their knowledge of advanced concepts and ability to perform production level tasks.  We expect all of our engineers to become journeymen over time.  As an alternative to portfolio work, a developer can use previous project or production work to satisfy all or part of these requirements.  Previous work needs to be reviewed and approved.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h4>Master</h4>
      <p>
        A master is one who has mastered the fundamental and advanced concepts of the skill area and is very skilled in their application.  They are a teacher and a mentor.  They often act in an architectural role helping to define our work patterns and in recommending technologies.  We rely on their judgment to help advance the discipline.
        If you desire to reach for this level, you would choose one or more areas of advanced study related to our work in FamilySearch and present a study plan.  In addition, you would choose a project that advances our front-end technologies and present a work plan.  It would be expected that this level would take a significant amount of calendar time because of the need to demonstrate both teaching and mentoring.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    "I try to remember that I am doing His work and as such I am entitled to receive divine help that may quicken my mind and enhance my natural abilities to do that which today may seem impossible.  When I live worthily and seek out experiences that invite the spirit of the Lord into my life, I feel empowered to do greater things and desire to live more fully by faith."
    Leadership Team
  </blockquote>

